    "story-origin": {
      "type": "text-and-image",
      "settings": {
        "image": "",
        "image_mask": "none",
        "subtitle": "",
        "title": "I didn't start this to build a brand.",
        "heading_size": "h2",
        "text": "<p>I started it because something didn't make sense. More people around me were dealing with gut issues, fatigue, things that didn't have clear answers. At the same time, food was becoming more processed, more packaged, more &ldquo;convenient.&rdquo; And somehow, that became normal. I didn't buy it.</p><p>So I started looking deeper.</p><p>Fermentation kept coming up. Not the version you see on shelves&mdash;but the real one. Salt. Vegetables. Time. Started small. Made mistakes. Threw batches away. Learned the hard way. And slowly, Tabchilli came together.</p>",
        "button_label": "",
        "button_link": "",
        "align_text": "left",
        "image_width": "50",
        "layout": "left",
        "divider": false,
        "top_padding": true,
        "bottom_padding": true
      }
    },
